{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01EQ7vUSkwcky8UsVzKt6d21","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information I need to provide a comprehensive report.\n\n## Codebase Exploration Report\n\n### 1. Overall Project Structure\n\n**Technology Stack:**\n- **Framework:** Spring Boot (parent: `core_business_v2`)\n- **ORM:** Spring Data JPA with Hibernate\n- **Database:** MariaDB (java client driver)\n- **Build Tool:** Maven 3\n- **Additional Libraries:** Lombok, Redisson (Redis), Spring WebFlux (reactive)\n- **Testing:** JUnit 5, TestContainers for integration tests\n\n**Top-level Directory Structure:**\n```\n/private/tmp/temper-arch/B/ingestion/\n├── pom.xml                          # Maven project file\n├── .mvn/                            # Maven wrapper\n├── src/\n│   ├── main/\n│   │   ├── java/com/fortinet/nac/ingestion/\n│   │   │   ├── IngestionApplication.java          (Spring Boot entry point)\n│   │   │   ├── controller/                         (REST endpoints)\n│   │   │   ├── service/                            (Business logic)\n│   │   │   ├── repository/                         (Data access)\n│   │   │   ├── entity/                             (JPA entities)\n│   │   │   ├── dto/                                (Data Transfer Objects)\n│   │   │   ├── config/                             (Spring configurations)\n│   │   │   ├── consumer/                           (Event consumer logic)\n│   │   │   ├── job/                                (Batch jobs)\n│   │   │   └── [other packages]\n│   │   └── resources/\n│   │       └── logback-spring.xml, application.properties\n│   └── test/java/                                  (Test classes)\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. Key Entity-Related Files\n\n#### **EntityController**\n📄 `/private/tmp/temper-arch/B/ingestion/src/main/java/com/fortinet/nac/ingestion/controller/EntityController.java` (Lines 1-103)\n\n**Key Patterns:**\n- **REST Endpoints:**\n  - `POST /api/v1/entities/query` - Query failed entities\n  - `GET /api/v1/entities/{id}` - Get entity by ID\n  - `GET /api/v1/entities/{id}/display-status` - Get entity display status\n  \n- **Dependency Injection:** Uses `@Resource` annotation (line 34) instead of `@Autowired`\n  ```java\n  @Resource\n  private EntityService entityService;\n  ```\n\n- **Critical Architectural Rule (lines 16-28):** \n  - **Controllers MUST NOT reference repository classes directly**\n  - All data access must go through `@Service` layer\n  - This enforces transaction boundaries, business validation, and tenant scoping\n  - See constraint comment starting at line 16\n\n#### **EntityRepository**\n📄 `/private/tmp/temper-arch/B/ingestion/src/main/java/com/fortinet/nac/ingestion/repository/EntityRepository.java` (Lines 1-124)\n\n**Type:** Spring Data JPA Interface extending `JpaRepository<Entity, Long>` and `JpaSpecificationExecutor<Entity>`\n\n**Key Methods:**\n- `findFirstByTypeAndHostIdentity(...)` (line 18)\n- `findFirstByTypeAndHostIdentityAndUserIdentity(...)` (line 20)\n- Custom `@Query` methods with `@Modifying` for updates:\n  - `updateInterrupted()` (lines 22-26)\n  - `updateProcessingState()` (lines 29-49)\n  - `findStuckEntities()` (lines 58-65)\n  - `markBatchForReprocess()` (lines 79-85)\n  - `claimInitEntityForReprocess()` (lines 107-113) - Atomic claim for reprocess\n  - `updateReprocessStateById()` (lines 116-123)\n\n**Advanced JPA Features:**\n- `@Modifying(clearAutomatically = true, flushAutomatically = true)` for proper transaction handling\n- Uses lightweight projections: `EntityProcessLockInfo` (line 93-102)\n- Pagination support via `Pageable` parameter\n\n#### **EntityService (Interface)**\n📄 `/private/tmp/temper-arch/B/ingestion/src/main/java/com/fortinet/nac/ingestion/service/EntityService.java` (Lines 1-54)\n\n**Key Methods:**\n- `getById(Long id)` (line 17)\n- `save(Entity entity)` / `saveBatch(...)` (lines 22-24)\n- `isInterrupted(long entityId)` (line 26)\n- `setInterrupted(Long entityId, boolean interrupted)` (line 28)\n- `queryFailedEntities(EntityQueryDTO req)` (line 34)\n- `isProcessingFinished(Long entityId)` (line 39)\n- `updateProcessingState(Entity fresh)` (line 41)\n- `findStuckEntities(Duration staleThreshold, int maxCount)` (line 43)\n- `markAllForReprocess()` (line 45)\n\n#### **EntityServiceImpl**\n📄 `/private/tmp/temper-arch/B/ingestion/src/main/java/com/fortinet/nac/ingestion/service/EntityServiceImpl.java` (Lines 1-150+)\n\n**Dependency Injection Pattern (lines 40-46):**\n```java\n@RequiredArgsConstructor  // Lombok annotation - constructor injection\npublic class EntityServiceImpl implements EntityService {\n    \n    private final EntityRepository entityRepository;\n    \n    @Qualifier(\"IngestionIdService\")\n    private final IdService idService;\n    \n    private final PlatformTransactionManager transactionManager;\n    private final MeterRegistry meterRegistry;\n    ...\n}\n```\n\n**Key Implementation Details:**\n- Uses `@Service` annotation (line 36)\n- Constructor injection with `@RequiredArgsConstructor` (Lombok)\n- Uses custom `IdService` (Snowflake ID generator) for ID generation (lines 64-66)\n- **Transactional boundaries:**\n  - `@Transactional(propagation = Propagation.REQUIRES_NEW)` for `setInterrupted()` (line 107)\n  - Guarantees state updates commit independently\n- **Metrics Integration:** Uses `MeterRegistry` for monitoring (lines 54-55)\n- **PostConstruct initialization:** Sets up Micrometer gauges (lines 52-55)\n\n---\n\n### 3. Existing Controller Files & Patterns\n\n#### **IngestionController**\n📄 `/private/tmp/temper-arch/B/ingestion/src/main/java/com/fortinet/nac/ingestion/controller/IngestionController.java` (Lines 1-100+)\n\n**Pattern: Reactive/WebFlux + Async Processing**\n```java\n@RestController\n@RequestMapping(\"/api/v1/ingestion\")\n@RequiredArgsConstructor\n@Slf4j\npublic class IngestionController {\n    \n    private final RedisStreamProducer producer;\n    private final IngestionCallbackRegistry callbackRegistry;\n    \n    @Autowired\n    @Qualifier(\"nettyOffloadExecutor\")\n    private ExecutorService nettyOffloadExecutor;\n    \n    @PostMapping(\"/events\")\n    public Mono<ResultDTO<?>> ingestEvent(@RequestBody @Validated IngestionRequest req) {\n        // Reactive Mono pattern with context and scheduling\n        return Mono.deferContextual(ctx -> { ... })\n            .subscribeOn(Schedulers.fromExecutor(nettyOffloadExecutor));\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Key Features:**\n- Uses `Mono<>` (Project Reactor) for async handling (line 43)\n- Manual thread pool offloading (line 86)\n- Request ID generation and tracing (lines 48-52)\n- Timeout handling with `CompletableFuture.orTimeout()` (lines 68-69)\n- Error handling with `onErrorResume()` (lines 87-97)\n\n#### **PolicyController**\n📄 `/private/tmp/temper-arch/B/ingestion/src/main/java/com/fortinet/nac/ingestion/controller/PolicyController.java` (Lines 1-84)\n\n**Pattern: Simple Service Call + Event Publishing**\n```java\n@RestController\n@RequestMapping(\"/api/v1/policy\")\n@RequiredArgsConstructor\n@Slf4j\npublic class PolicyController {\n    \n    private final EntityService entityService;\n    private final ApplicationEventPublisher eventPublisher;\n    \n    @PostMapping(\"/apply-existing-entities\")\n    public ResultDTO<MarkForReprocessResponse> applyExistingEntities() {\n        MarkForReprocessResult markResult = entityService.markAllForReprocess();\n        eventPublisher.publishEvent(new PolicyReprocessRequestedEvent(...));\n        return ResultDTO.success(...);\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Key Features:**\n- Constructor injection with `@RequiredArgsConstructor` (line 17)\n- Service layer injection (line 21)\n- Event publication pattern (line 37)\n- Detailed response DTOs (lines 58-66)\n- Exception handling with try-catch (lines 29-82)\n\n#### **FingerprintController**\n📄 `/private/tmp/temper-arch/B/ingestion/src/main/java/com/fortinet/nac/ingestion/controller/FingerprintController.java` (Lines 1-25)\n\n**Pattern: Simple Service Delegation**\n```java\n@RestController\n@RequestMapping(\"/api/v1/fingerprint\")\n@RequiredArgsConstructor\npublic class FingerprintController {\n    \n    private final FingerprintService fingerprintService;\n    \n    @PostMapping(\"/calculate\")\n    public ResultDTO<String> calc(@RequestBody FingerprintRequestDTO req) {\n        String fp = fingerprintService.buildFingerprint(req);\n        return ResultDTO.success(fp);\n    }\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. Framework & Version Details\n\n**Spring Boot Configuration:**\n- **Parent POM:** `core_business_v2` version `0.0.1-SNAPSHOT`\n- **Key Dependencies:**\n  - `spring-boot-starter-data-jpa` (JPA/Hibernate)\n  - `spring-boot-starter-webflux` (Reactive)\n  - `spring-boot-starter-validation` (Bean validation)\n  - `spring-boot-starter-test` (JUnit 5)\n  - Redisson (Redis client)\n  - TestContainers (integration testing)\n\n**Application Entry Point:**\n📄 `/private/tmp/temper-arch/B/ingestion/src/main/java/com/fortinet/nac/ingestion/IngestionApplication.java`\n```java\n@EnableAsync\n@EnableScheduling\n@SpringBootApplication(scanBasePackages = \"com.fortinet.nac\")\npublic class IngestionApplication { ... }\n```\n\n---\n\n### 5. Dependency Injection Patterns\n\n**Three Main Patterns Observed:**\n\n1. **Constructor Injection with Lombok (Recommended)**\n   - Used in `EntityServiceImpl`, `PolicyController`, `FingerprintController`\n   - Pattern:\n     ```java\n     @RequiredArgsConstructor\n     public class MyClass {\n         private final SomeDependency dep;\n     }\n     ```\n\n2. **Field Injection (Less Common but Used)**\n   - Used in `EntityController`\n   - Pattern:\n     ```java\n     @Resource\n     private EntityService entityService;\n     ```\n\n3. **Qualifier Annotation**\n   - Used for custom bean identification\n   - Examples:\n     ```java\n     @Qualifier(\"IngestionIdService\")\n     private final IdService idService;\n     \n     @Qualifier(\"nettyOffloadExecutor\")\n     private ExecutorService nettyOffloadExecutor;\n     ```\n\n---\n\n### 6. Configuration Classes\n\n#### **IdGeneratorConfig**\n📄 `/private/tmp/temper-arch/B/ingestion/src/main/java/com/fortinet/nac/ingestion/config/IdGeneratorConfig.java`\n\n- Uses **Snowflake ID Generator** (distributed unique ID generation)\n- Bean named `\"ingestionIdGenerator\"` exposed as `PersistenceSnowflakeIdGenerator`\n- Configuration properties:\n  - `id.generator.data-center-id` (default: 0)\n  - `id.generator.worker-id` (default: 0)\n  - `id.generator.data-server-id` (default: \"ingest\")\n  - Module: 7\n\n#### **NettyOffLoadThreadPoolConfig**\n📄 `/private/tmp/temper-arch/B/ingestion/src/main/java/com/fortinet/nac/ingestion/config/NettyOffLoadThreadPoolConfig.java`\n\n- Configurable thread pool for reactive/WebFlux tasks\n- Bean: `\"nettyOffloadExecutor\"` - `ExecutorService`\n- **Thread Pool Parameters:**\n  - Core size: configurable (default: 30)\n  - Max size: configurable (default: 300)\n  - Queue capacity: configurable (default: 10,000)\n  - Keep-alive: configurable (default: 60s)\n- **Metrics Integration:** Binds to Micrometer for monitoring:\n  - Active threads gauge\n  - Pool size gauge\n  - Queue size gauge\n  - Task completion tracking\n\n---\n\n### 7. JPA Entity Pattern\n\n**Entity.java** 📄 `/private/tmp/temper-arch/B/ingestion/src/main/java/com/fortinet/nac/ingestion/entity/Entity.java`\n\n**Annotations Used:**\n```java\n@Data                          // Lombok: getter/setter/equals/hashCode\n@Builder                       // Lombok: builder pattern\n@NoArgsConstructor             // Lombok: default constructor\n@AllArgsConstructor            // Lombok: all-args constructor\n@javax.persistence.Entity      // JPA entity marker\n@Table(name = \"entities\")      // Database table mapping\n```\n\n**Key Columns:**\n- `@Id` on `id` (Long) - primary key\n- `@Enumerated(EnumType.STRING)` for `type` (EntityType enum)\n- `@Enumerated(EnumType.STRING)` for `reproces